1.text: Start with neatly brushed, dry or damp hair.

2.text: Brush your hair straight back, then gather a section from the hairline.

3.text: Split the section into 3 equal strands.

4.text: Begin a standard braid to anchor the Dutch braid.

5.text: Add a thin section of hair to the right strand before crossing it under the middle one.

6.text: Repeat the process on the left side.

7.text: Continue to Dutch braid until you reach the nape of your neck.

8.text: Finish off with a standard braid.

9.text: Loosen the outer strands of the braid to make it fuller, if desired.

11.text: Part your hair down the center for a symmetrical look.

12.text: Make a side part for a cool, off-center style.

13.text: Gather a thin section of hair from the left side.

14.text: Split the section into 3 equal strands.

16.text: Add some hair to the left strand, then cross it under.

17.text: Repeat the process for the right strand.

18.text: Continue to Dutch braid until you reach your nape.

19.text: Finish off with a regular braid.

20.text: Repeat the process on the other side of your head.

21.text: Wrap or twist the braids into a bun or crown, if desired.
